### Testbench

To reproduce, you can run this testbench:
```
#include "cxxrtl.cpp"

#include <iostream>

int main() {

  cxxrtl_design::p_wrapper__cxxrtl top;

  top.p_in__0.set<uint32_t>(0);
  top.p_in__1.set<uint32_t>(0);
  top.p_in__2.set<uint32_t>(0);

  top.step();

  std::cout << "Testbench complete!" << std::endl;

  exit(0);
}
```

### Design

Here is the design, split between a wrapper for 32-bit integers and the actual design:

`wrapper_cxxrtl.sv`:
```
